{
  "message": "Restore early-return loading pattern and add Streamdown to bead modal\n\nTwo changes to the BeadsView component:\n\n1. Structural: Reverts the unified ternary render tree\n   ({loading ? <spinner/> : <content/>}) back to an early-return\n   pattern (if (loading) return <spinner/>). This moves the Script\n   tags so they only render once loading is complete, matching the\n   original architecture where the loading spinner is a standalone\n   return and the main content (including vendor script loaders)\n   renders as a flat structure without wrapper indentation. The UI\n   is identical\u2014this is purely a code organization preference that\n   reduces nesting depth in the main return.\n\n2. Content: The bead detail modal's Synapse_Descriptor section now\n   renders through the Streamdown component instead of raw string\n   interpolation, enabling Markdown formatting (code blocks, bold,\n   links) in bead descriptions pulled from the SQLite database.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
